114
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:52,020
I'll report to him about it.

115
00:14:55,580 --> 00:14:57,020
I didn't mean to offend this place.

116
00:14:58,180 --> 00:14:59,180
I saw

117
00:14:59,660 --> 00:15:01,260
the students in the library
were all very busy.

118
00:15:01,980 --> 00:15:03,380
I didn't know what had happened.

119
00:15:03,820 --> 00:15:05,020
So I came out to take a look.

120
00:15:05,660 --> 00:15:06,900
However, I got lost.

121
00:15:08,260 --> 00:15:09,100
They were looking for

122
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:11,340
the child in white

123
00:15:11,340 --> 00:15:12,180
the Magistrate mentioned.

124
00:15:13,580 --> 00:15:14,620
Have they found him?

125
00:15:17,020 --> 00:15:18,900
Following the direction
the Magistrate told us,

126
00:15:18,900 --> 00:15:20,580
they searched the entire yard.

127
00:15:20,780 --> 00:15:22,540
But they didn't find the child.

128
00:15:25,620 --> 00:15:26,900
Well,

129
00:15:27,300 --> 00:15:29,540
the Magistrate was hurt
by poisonous thorns.

130
00:15:29,980 --> 00:15:30,940
Was it possible

131
00:15:32,060 --> 00:15:33,420
that he was hallucinating?

132
00:15:36,020 --> 00:15:36,860
I don't think

133
00:15:38,340 --> 00:15:40,460
the Magistrate was hallucinating.

134
00:15:43,260 --> 00:15:44,220
Instead, he saw a ghost.

135
00:15:46,180 --> 00:15:47,220
Or the Magistrate

136
00:15:47,740 --> 00:15:49,100
saw something

137
00:15:49,420 --> 00:15:50,900
that did not exist

138
00:15:51,340 --> 00:15:53,100
because of the foul aura of the dead.

139
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:57,180
Do you know there will be
a solar eclipse this month?

140
00:15:57,820 --> 00:15:59,420
On such dismal days,

141
00:16:01,140 --> 00:16:02,420
the dead here

142
00:16:03,940 --> 00:16:05,500
